OL,3,CPolice could be given new powers to
OL,4,Ccrackdown on drug-impaired driving
OL,6,FChanges to Jersey's road traffic law
OL,7,Fcould make it easier to prosecute
OL,8,Fthose who drive under the influence of
OL,9,Fdrugs.
OL,11,FIn the changes proposed by Jersey's
OL,12,FInfrastructure Minister, Constable
OL,13,FAndy Jehan, islanders could face legal
OL,14,Flimits and roadside tests.
OL,16,FUnder the current law, there is no
OL,17,Fstatutory definition of legal limits
OL,18,Ffor drug concentration, and police do
OL,19,Fnot have the power to undertake
OL,20,Froadside tests for drugs.
