OL,3,CPolice could be given new powers to
OL,4,Ccrackdown on drug-impaired driving
OL,6,FIn the Draft Road Traffic Law report,
OL,7,FMr Jehan says this "limits the ability
OL,8,Fof the police to successfully
OL,9,Fprosecute individuals driving under
OL,10,Fthe influence, even where impairment
OL,11,Fis suspected".
OL,13,FHe outlines: "The lack of evidential
OL,14,Fthresholds creates ambiguity in
OL,15,Fenforcement, undermines deterrence,
OL,16,Fand has made successful prosecutions
OL,17,Fchallenging."
